# Coding Conventions

## PHP Standards
- Follow PSR-12 coding standards strictly.
- Use strict typing where possible (`declare(strict_types=1);` and scalar type hints).
- Prefer constructor property promotion for dependency injection.

## Laravel Specifics
- Use Route Model Binding instead of manually querying IDs in controllers.
- Use Dependency Injection rather than relying heavily on global facades or helper functions (e.g., use `Illuminate\Http\Request` instead of `request()`).
- Keep controllers thin. Move heavy business logic into Action classes or Services.
- Always use early returns to avoid deeply nested conditionals.
